14:05.627 --> 14:06.671
ROMEO AND JULIET.

14:06.715 --> 14:09.457
YOU KNOW HOW OLD SHE WAS? 13.

14:09.500 --> 14:11.415
SO HOW COME WITH HER,
IT'’S THIS GREAT ROMANCE,

14:11.459 --> 14:14.070
BUT WHEN IT WAS
ME AND BRANDI,
I'’M A PERVERT?

14:14.114 --> 14:15.942
NOW, MY SHAKESPEARE'’S
A LITTLE RUSTY,

14:15.985 --> 14:18.945
BUT I DON'’T REMEMBER ROMEO
BEING A 50-YEAR-OLD DEGENERATE

14:18.988 --> 14:20.903
WHO COLLECTS GIRLS'’ UNDERWEAR.

14:20.947 --> 14:22.818
PRENTISS: YOU DIDN'’T ANSWER
MY QUESTION, MR. BRODIE.

14:22.862 --> 14:26.213
WHERE WERE YOU LAST NIGHT
BETWEEN THE HOURS
OF 9 P.M. AND 4 A.M.?

14:26.256 --> 14:28.955
AT HOME WITH MY MOM.

14:28.998 --> 14:30.782
CALL AND ASK.

14:30.826 --> 14:32.045
NOW, IF YOU'’RE NOT
GONNA CHARGE ME

14:32.088 --> 14:33.524
WITH ANYTHING,
THEN I'’M--

14:33.568 --> 14:35.091
OH, WE'’RE DEFINITELY GONNA
CHARGE YOU WITH SOMETHING.

14:35.135 --> 14:38.312
PAROLE VIOLATION,
ASSAULT ON A FEDERAL AGENT.

14:38.355 --> 14:39.791
THAT SHOULD GET
THE BALL ROLLING.

14:39.835 --> 14:41.097
WAIT.

14:41.141 --> 14:43.273
I'’M GOING TO JAIL?

14:43.317 --> 14:44.535
WELL, LOOK AT IT THIS WAY.

14:44.579 --> 14:46.755
SOMEONE ASKS YOU
WHEREFORE ART THOU,

14:46.798 --> 14:49.018
YOU KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

14:50.759 --> 14:53.196
OK, SO WE HAVE
A CITYWIDE CURFEW
IN PLACE TONIGHT.

14:53.240 --> 14:54.719
I HEARD THE GOOD
NEWS ABOUT BRODIE.

14:54.763 --> 14:56.286
I'’M SCHEDULING
A PRESS CONFERENCE
TO ANNOUNCE

14:56.330 --> 14:58.549
THAT WE HAVE OUR
PRIMARY SUSPECT
IN CUSTODY.

14:58.593 --> 15:00.987
THAT'’S A LITTLE
PREMATURE, MAYOR.

15:01.030 --> 15:02.945
WHY?

15:02.989 --> 15:05.469
WELL, BECAUSE PEOPLE
ARE GONNA THINK
THE DANGER IS PASSED.

15:05.513 --> 15:06.601
IT HASN'’T.

15:06.644 --> 15:07.907
BRODIE'’S STILL
A PERSON OF INTEREST,

15:07.950 --> 15:10.474
BUT HIS VAN CAME BACK
CLEAN AND HE HAS AN ALIBI.

15:10.518 --> 15:13.303
YOU MEAN HIS MOM?

15:13.347 --> 15:15.349
AND THE ONLY REASON
THE VAN IS CLEAN

15:15.392 --> 15:17.481
IS BECAUSE HE
CLEANED IT.

15:17.525 --> 15:19.919
WE'’LL HOLD A PRESS CONFERENCE
WHEN IT'’S APPROPRIATE.

15:19.962 --> 15:21.268
OH, GOOD.

15:21.311 --> 15:22.834
WHEN WOULD THAT BE,

15:22.878 --> 15:26.229
WHEN THE NEXT BATCH
OF KIDS GOES MISSING?

15:26.273 --> 15:28.014
UNBELIEVABLE.

15:29.363 --> 15:31.147
HMM.

15:31.191 --> 15:34.585
LOOK, I KNOW HE WANTS
TO TIE THIS ALL OFF
IN A TIDY BOW, BUT COME ON.

15:34.629 --> 15:36.761
YOU THINK BRODIE'’S
OUR GUY?

15:36.805 --> 15:39.155
NO, NO.
THE GUY'’S A MORON.

15:39.199 --> 15:41.636
AND MORONS DON'’T
GRAB CHILDREN?

15:41.679 --> 15:43.203
YEAH, BUT THIS UNSUB
ISN'’T GRABBING.

15:43.246 --> 15:44.769
THE KIDS ARE GOING TO HIM.

15:44.813 --> 15:46.684
FOR AN OFFENDER TO SINK
IN THEIR HOOKS THAT DEEP

15:46.728 --> 15:48.991
REQUIRES PATIENCE,
PLANNING, AND SMARTS,

15:49.035 --> 15:50.601
NONE OF WHICH IS BRODIE.

15:50.645 --> 15:51.994
AT LEAST THIS TOWN'’S
ON HIGH ALERT.

15:52.038 --> 15:53.648
I DOUBT THERE'’S A DOOR
IN WESSER, IOWA

15:53.691 --> 15:55.476
THAT HASN'’T BEEN DOUBLE-
AND TRIPLE-BOLTED.

15:55.519 --> 15:57.521
LET'’S HOPE THAT'S ENOUGH.

17:36.446 --> 17:38.100
THE UNSUB'’S SENDING
A MESSAGE--

17:38.144 --> 17:40.581
"TAKE ALL THE PRECAUTIONS
YOU WANT, I CAN STILL
GET YOUR KIDS."

17:40.624 --> 17:42.887
KATIE'’S FATHER NOT
ONLY DOUBLE-LOCKED
THE FRONT DOOR,

17:42.931 --> 17:44.759
HE BARRICADED IT
WITH A COUCH.

17:44.802 --> 17:46.282
DID THEIR DAUGHTER KNOW ANY
OF THE OTHER MISSING KIDS?

17:46.326 --> 17:47.718
NO, SHE WAS
HOMESCHOOLED.

17:47.762 --> 17:49.459
THESE KIDS ARE LINKED SOMEHOW.

17:49.503 --> 17:52.332
WE NEED TO WIDEN OUT,
LOOK INTO EXTRACURRICULAR
ACTIVITIES--

17:52.375 --> 17:54.986
SPORTS, SUMMER CAMPS.

17:55.030 --> 17:56.814
THE KIDS ON THE
SURVEILLANCE VIDEO,

17:56.858 --> 17:59.513
THEY LOOKED LIKE THEY WERE
ON AUTO

17:59.556 --> 18:00.818
MORE LIKE ZOMBIFIED.

18:00.862 --> 18:03.734
BUT KATIE'’S PARENTS
PUT UP A BARRICADE.

18:03.778 --> 18:08.043
SO SHE WAS FORCED
TO USE IN-THE-MOMENT
COGNITIVE SKILLS

18:08.087 --> 18:09.610
TO CIRCUMVENT THE OBSTACLE.

18:09.653 --> 18:12.178
EVALUATE, PROBLEM-SOLVE,
IMPROVISE.

18:12.221 --> 18:14.005
NOT YOUR AVERAGE
ZOMBIE'’S STRONG SUIT.

18:14.049 --> 18:15.529
MAKING IT EVEN MORE
LIKELY THAT THE UNSUB

18:15.572 --> 18:17.792
HAD PREVIOUS
PERSONAL INTERACTIONS
WITH THE CHILDREN.

18:17.835 --> 18:21.056
THE UNSUB DROPPED
A PACKET OFF AT
THE LOCAL NEWSPAPER.

18:21.100 --> 18:22.275
IT'’S ON ITS WAY HERE NOW.

18:27.367 --> 18:30.239
I'’M SO COLD.

18:30.283 --> 18:32.589
IT'’LL BE WARMER IF WE
SIT CLOSE TOGETHER.

18:32.633 --> 18:34.939
COME ON.

18:41.903 --> 18:43.948
IT WAS FOUND OUTSIDE
THE NEWSPAPER OFFICES.

18:43.992 --> 18:45.385
NOBODY SAW WHO LEFT IT.

18:45.428 --> 18:48.649
NAMES OF
THE FIRST 3 KIDS.

18:51.391 --> 18:53.175
NAIL CLIPPINGS.

18:53.219 --> 18:56.439
SO WHY SEND PROOF OF LIFE
WITH NO RANSOM DEMAND?

18:56.483 --> 18:59.312
THERE WAS A FLASH DRIVE
IN THE ENVELOPE, TOO.

19:01.575 --> 19:05.927
MAN, ON TAPE:
HOW DOES IT FEEL?

19:05.970 --> 19:08.190
WHAT DID HE SAY?

19:08.234 --> 19:09.931
HOW DOES IT FEEL?

19:09.974 --> 19:14.544
OUR UNSUB USED THE EXPRESSION
"HOW DOES IT FEEL?"

19:14.588 --> 19:17.504
THIS INDICATES THAT,
WHILE HE ABDUCTED THE KIDS,

19:17.547 --> 19:19.897
OUR UNSUB'’S ANGER IS
FOCUSED ON SOMEONE ELSE.

19:19.941 --> 19:22.073
ALVEZ: IT ALSO EXPLAINS
WHY THERE APPEARS TO BE

19:22.117 --> 19:23.771
NO DELIBERATE HARM
TO THE CHILDREN.

19:23.814 --> 19:26.208
THE KIDS ARE MERELY
A MEANS TO AN END.

19:26.252 --> 19:28.297
HE'’S NOT A SEXUAL PREDATOR
NOR A KIDNAPPER

19:28.341 --> 19:29.690
IN A TRADITIONAL SENSE.

19:29.733 --> 19:31.996
THIS PERSON IS AN
INJUSTICE COLLECTOR,

19:32.040 --> 19:34.390
AND AS SUCH IS
MOTIVATED BY REVENGE.

19:34.434 --> 19:36.175
REID: NONE OF THE CHILDREN'’S
PARENTS, HOWEVER,

19:36.218 --> 19:39.090
ARE IN PROFESSIONS
THAT TYPICALLY EVOKE
REVENGE-BASED ANGER--

19:39.134 --> 19:41.223
DOCTORS, JUDGES, LAWYERS.

19:41.267 --> 19:42.572
ROSSI: WE BELIEVE THE UNSUB IS

19:42.616 --> 19:44.661
IN HIS MID-30s TO MID-40s.

19:44.705 --> 19:47.577
HE'’S THOROUGH, INTELLIGENT,
AND CALCULATING.

19:47.621 --> 19:49.927
HE MAY HAVE ALSO SUFFERED
THE LOSS OF A CHILD RECENTLY.

19:49.971 --> 19:52.408
THAT COULD BE WHAT'’S
TRIGGERED THESE
CURRENT ABDUCTIONS.

19:52.452 --> 19:54.454
NOW, WHETHER THIS WAS
A LITERAL DEATH,

19:54.497 --> 19:58.327
A PHYSICAL SEPARATION,
OR PURELY A SYMBOLIC LOSS
ISN'’T CLEAR.

19:58.371 --> 19:59.807
SIMMONS: THE CHILDREN
ARE APPARENTLY RESPONDING

19:59.850 --> 20:02.940
TO A FORM OF POST-HYPNOTIC
SUGGESTION.

20:02.984 --> 20:04.594
LEWIS: HE'’S ALSO
TECHNOLOGICAL SAVVY

20:04.638 --> 20:06.379
AND CAPABLE OF BONDING
WITH CHILDREN.

20:06.422 --> 20:08.381
IN FACT, HIS CYBER
EXPERTISE MAY BE

20:08.424 --> 20:09.730
HIS ENTREÉE INTO
THEIR WORLD.

20:09.773 --> 20:11.122
REID: AND THIS PERSON IS
KNOWN TO YOUR CHILDREN,

20:11.166 --> 20:13.168
AND HE MIGHT EVEN
BE KNOWN TO YOU.

20:13.212 --> 20:15.779
HE IS A LOCAL
AND NOT A TRANSIENT,

20:15.823 --> 20:17.825
WHICH WILL MAKE
IDENTIFYING HIM
EVEN MORE DIFFICULT.

20:17.868 --> 20:20.131
HYPERVIGILANCE IS KEY.

20:20.175 --> 20:22.960
IT'’S NOT ENOUGH TO LOCK
THE DOORS AND THE WINDOWS.

20:23.004 --> 20:25.267
ADULTS CANNOT TAKE THEIR
EYES OFF OF CHILDREN,

20:25.311 --> 20:26.399
NOT EVEN FOR A MINUTE.

20:26.442 --> 20:28.575
PRENTISS: EVEN IF YOU
THINK YOUR KIDS

20:28.618 --> 20:30.490
ARE SECURE AND PROTECTED,

20:30.533 --> 20:32.753
THIS UNSUB HAS
DEMONSTRATED TO US
THAT THEY ARE NOT.

20:32.796 --> 20:35.669
THANK YOU.

20:53.295 --> 20:56.298
AHEM.

20:56.342 --> 20:58.126
GOOD.
MM-HMM.

20:58.169 --> 20:59.214
MM-HMM.

20:59.258 --> 21:01.782
SO, UM,
I GOT A CALL

21:01.825 --> 21:04.175
FROM YOUR
INSURANCE ADJUSTOR.

21:04.219 --> 21:05.568
MM-HMM.

21:05.612 --> 21:08.005
HE WAS CALLING TO CONFIRM

21:08.049 --> 21:10.660
THAT YOU HAD
DECLINED A BENEFIT.

21:10.704 --> 21:14.316
YOUR POLICY PROVIDES
A GENEROUS RENTAL ALLOWANCE

21:14.360 --> 21:16.275
IF YOU'’RE DISPLACED
FROM YOUR HOME.

21:19.495 --> 21:20.670
SO NOW YOU KNOW.

21:20.714 --> 21:24.326
MOM, WHY WOULD YOU
MAKE UP THAT STORY

21:24.370 --> 21:26.328
THAT YOU HAD NO
OTHER OPTIONS?

21:26.372 --> 21:29.244
BECAUSE I WANTED TO
SPEND TIME WITH YOU,

21:29.288 --> 21:32.595
AND I WAS AFRAID IF I ASKED,
YOU WOULD TELL ME NO.

21:32.639 --> 21:34.075
WHY WOULD I DO THAT?

21:34.118 --> 21:35.511
OH, COME ON, JJ.

21:35.555 --> 21:38.209
YOU ARE PERFECTLY
HAPPY UP HERE

21:38.253 --> 21:40.603
WITH YOUR LIFE
JUST AS IT IS.

21:40.647 --> 21:42.866
THE SAME WAY YOU
ARE PERFECTLY HAPPY

21:42.910 --> 21:46.043
WITH YOUR LIFE IN
EAST ALLEGHENY, RIGHT?
IT DOES NOT MEAN THAT--

21:46.087 --> 21:47.697
OH, YOU THINK I'’M HAPPY?

21:47.741 --> 21:48.916
YOU THINK I'’M HAPPY

21:48.959 --> 21:51.701
IN THAT HOUSE ALL ALONE,

21:51.745 --> 21:54.704
YOUR DAD OFF WITH
HIS NEW WIFE,

21:54.748 --> 21:57.968
ONE DAUGHTER
WHO NEVER SAW 17,

21:58.012 --> 21:59.622
AND THE OTHER...

22:02.190 --> 22:05.498
THE OTHER WHAT, MOM?

22:05.541 --> 22:07.369
THE OTHER WHAT?

22:07.413 --> 22:09.066
WHO LEFT.

22:09.110 --> 22:11.939
WHO WENT AWAY
AND STAYED AWAY.

22:11.982 --> 22:13.854
I CAME BACK.

22:13.897 --> 22:15.551
YEAH, AFTER 20 YEARS.

22:15.595 --> 22:18.119
CAN YOU BLAME ME? LOOK,

22:18.162 --> 22:20.817
THE TERRIBLE MEMORIES,
WHAT HAPPENED TO ROZ,

22:20.861 --> 22:22.950
THEY'’RE...

22:22.993 --> 22:25.039
IT'’S ALL THERE...

22:25.082 --> 22:27.258
IN THAT PLACE.

22:27.302 --> 22:29.260
WELL, I'’M THERE,
TOO, REMEMBER?

22:32.873 --> 22:36.267
LEWIS: WELL, WE'’RE
CHECKING EVERY INDUSTRIAL
SPACE IN THE AREA.

22:36.311 --> 22:37.921
SO FAR NOTHING.

22:37.965 --> 22:40.141
LOOK AT THIS PHOTO FROM
KATIE LINZ'’S BEDROOM.

22:40.184 --> 22:42.404
SHE WAS MAKING SOMETHING
OUT OF PAPIER-MACHE,

22:42.448 --> 22:44.885
JUST LIKE JOEY PRYOR.

22:44.928 --> 22:46.408
SCHOOL PROJECT, MAYBE.

22:46.452 --> 22:49.063
NO, NO, KATIE
WAS HOMESCHOOLED.

22:49.106 --> 22:50.281
I'’LL HAVE GARCIA
LOOK INTO IT.

22:50.325 --> 22:52.327
YEAH.

22:52.371 --> 22:56.113
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION
IN ADJACENT ROOM]

22:56.157 --> 22:57.941
WELL, THE SUN'’S GOING DOWN.

22:57.985 --> 23:01.205
EVERY LAST PATROL OFFICER'’S
WALKING THE STREETS.

23:01.249 --> 23:03.773
THIS LITTLE TOWN'’S
TURNED INTO A FORTRESS.

23:03.817 --> 23:06.689
THINK THE UNSUB
WILL BE DISCOURAGED?

23:06.733 --> 23:08.778
YEAH, ME, NEITHER.

23:10.911 --> 23:13.740
WOMAN: WELL, HOW MUCH
LONGER WILL YOU BE?

23:13.783 --> 23:16.917
NO, NO. I'’M JUST
MAKING UP A SPARE BED.

23:16.960 --> 23:18.440
TIMMY'’S SLEEPING IN
OUR ROOM TONIGHT,

23:18.484 --> 23:20.573
WHETHER HE LIKES IT OR NOT.

23:20.616 --> 23:23.358
MOM, WHY CAN'’T
I WATCH TV?

23:23.402 --> 23:26.187
LISTEN, I NEED TO
GET STARTED ON DINNER.

23:26.230 --> 23:28.102
LOVE YOU, TOO.

23:37.416 --> 23:39.113
SOMEBODY'’S AT THE DOOR.

24:01.483 --> 24:03.529
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

24:07.707 --> 24:10.013
WHAT'’S GOING ON?

24:10.057 --> 24:12.189
THERE'’S A DISTURBANCE
AT THE MAYOR'’S HOUSE.

24:12.233 --> 24:14.496
A NEIGHBOR SAID SHE
HEARD A CHILD SCREAM.

24:40.566 --> 24:42.785
REID: CALL AN AMBULANCE.

24:48.356 --> 24:50.053
IT'’S OK.
HELP IS ON THE WAY.

24:54.101 --> 24:57.234
ROSSI: AMBULANCE
IS ALMOST HERE.

24:57.278 --> 24:59.933
IT'’S TOO LATE.

24:59.976 --> 25:01.587
SHE'’S ALREADY DEAD.

25:10.160 --> 25:12.075
[FIRE AND RESCUE RADIO
TRANSMISSIONS]

25:17.820 --> 25:19.692
SIMMONS: WHAT THE
HELL HAPPENED HERE?

25:19.735 --> 25:22.956
MRS. TREMAINE'’S SKULL
WAS CRUSHED,
AND THE BOY'’S MISSING.

25:22.999 --> 25:24.348
THAT'’S A BIG CHANGE
IN M.O.,

25:24.392 --> 25:26.568
BUT THIS HAD TO HAVE
BEEN OUR UNSUB.

25:26.612 --> 25:28.396
JUDGING BY
THE VOLUME OF BLOOD,

25:28.439 --> 25:30.485
SHE WAS MOST LIKELY
ATTACKED HERE
AND LEFT FOR DEAD.

25:30.529 --> 25:32.574
BUT I THOUGHT
MRS. TREMAINE

25:32.618 --> 25:34.141
WAS IN THE KITCHEN
FIXING DINNER.

25:34.184 --> 25:36.709
THAT WAS AFTER THE ATTACK.

25:36.752 --> 25:38.754
COME AGAIN.

25:38.798 --> 25:40.756
HER NEOCORTEX WAS
DESTROYED,

25:40.800 --> 25:43.367
BUT HER PALEOCORTEX
MUST HAVE REMAINED INTACT.

25:43.411 --> 25:45.108
IT'’S THE MORE PRIMITIVE
PART OF THE BRAIN

25:45.152 --> 25:47.241
THAT GUIDES INSTINCT
AND HABITUAL ACTION.

25:47.284 --> 25:51.071
ROSSI: LIKE WHEN IT'’S
DINNERTIME, YOU GO FIX DINNER.

25:51.114 --> 25:55.423
OK. WELL, THAT'’S A SHARP
ESCALATION OF VIOLENCE.

25:55.466 --> 25:59.079
AND THE UNSUB DIDN'’T
TRY TO LURE TIMMY OUT
LIKE HE DID THE OTHERS.

25:59.122 --> 26:00.428
OR HE TRIED AND FAILED.

26:00.471 --> 26:01.603
MAN: MAYOR,
YOU CAN'’T GO IN--

26:01.647 --> 26:03.953
MAYOR: IT'’S MY HOUSE.
LET ME IN.

26:03.997 --> 26:05.651
THEY SAID, UH...

26:15.356 --> 26:16.966
JOAN IS DEAD.

26:17.010 --> 26:18.272
MAYOR--

26:20.013 --> 26:21.754
WHERE'’S MY BOY?

26:28.543 --> 26:29.936
HE'’S GONE, ISN'T HE?

26:29.979 --> 26:32.460
WE'’RE GONNA FIND
YOUR SON.

26:32.503 --> 26:33.940
YOU HAVE MY WORD
ON THAT.

26:33.983 --> 26:36.856
MAYOR TREMAINE, I KNOW
IT'’S DIFFICULT

26:36.899 --> 26:38.379
TO THINK CLEARLY
RIGHT NOW,

26:38.422 --> 26:40.860
BUT IT'’S INCREDIBLY
IMPORTANT THAT WE KNOW

26:40.903 --> 26:42.862
IF TIMMY HAD A CELL PHONE
OR A COMPUTER.

26:42.905 --> 26:44.690
YEAH.

26:46.300 --> 26:48.389
IT'’S UPSTAIRS
IN MY OFFICE.

26:48.432 --> 26:49.608
IT'’S IN YOUR OFFICE?

26:49.651 --> 26:50.826
MAYOR: TIMMY DIDN'’T
DO HIS CHORES,

26:50.870 --> 26:54.047
SO WE TOOK IT AWAY
FOR A FEW DAYS.

26:54.090 --> 26:55.265
SIMMONS: OK.

26:55.309 --> 26:56.876
LET'’S GET YOU
OUT OF HERE.

26:56.919 --> 26:59.400
OK? COME ON.

27:03.839 --> 27:05.624
WELL, THAT EXPLAINS IT.

27:05.667 --> 27:07.147
THE KIDS ARE BEING
LURED VIA THE INTERNET,

27:07.190 --> 27:08.714
BUT TIMMY WAS OFFLINE.

27:08.757 --> 27:13.370
SO THE UNSUB GOT AN AX
AND WENT BACK TO BASICS.

27:13.414 --> 27:16.417
SO THE WIFE AND THE
SON OF THE MAYOR.

27:16.460 --> 27:17.897
THAT CAN'’T BE
A COINCIDENCE.

27:17.940 --> 27:19.855
YEAH, AND THE PACKET WAS
SENT TO THE TOWN NEWSPAPER.

27:19.899 --> 27:21.248
I MEAN, THIS UNSUB'’S
ANGER ISN'’T DIRECTED

27:21.291 --> 27:23.032
AT ANY SPECIFIC PARENTS.

27:23.076 --> 27:25.208
HE'’S GOT A GRUDGE
AGAINST THE TOWN AS A WHOLE.

27:25.252 --> 27:27.210
GARCIA, WHAT HAVE
YOU GOT?

27:27.254 --> 27:29.865
IT TURNS OUT THAT JOEY PRYOR
AND KATIE LINZ

27:29.909 --> 27:32.259
TOOK A PAPIER-MACHE CLASS
TOGETHER AS PART

27:32.302 --> 27:33.782
OF THIS SUMMER
ACTIVITIES PROGRAM

27:33.826 --> 27:35.784
LOCATED AT
THE COUNTY FAIRGROUNDS.

27:35.828 --> 27:37.656
NOW, I KNOW WHAT YOU'’RE
THINKING, AND BEFORE YOU ASK--

27:37.699 --> 27:40.223
I'’M SORRY--THE INSTRUCTOR
WAS A RETIRED NURSE

27:40.267 --> 27:41.747
IN HER SEVENTIES.

27:41.790 --> 27:43.226
THAT'’S ABOUT AS UN-UNSUBBY
AS THEY COME.

27:43.270 --> 27:45.011
WERE THE OTHER KIDS ENROLLED?

27:45.054 --> 27:46.577
GARCIA: NOT IN THAT CLASS,

27:46.621 --> 27:48.057
BUT IN THAT ACTIVITIES
PROGRAM, YES.

27:48.101 --> 27:50.973
LET'’S SEE. AIDEN LYSON WAS
TAKING A WOODWORKING COURSE.

27:51.017 --> 27:53.628
OLIVIA WOOLSEY
WENT THE 4-H ROUTE,
LEARNING ABOUT CHICKENS.

27:53.672 --> 27:55.412
OK, SO THE UNSUB
CHERRY PICKED THE KIDS

27:55.456 --> 27:56.849
FROM THE OTHER CLASSES.

27:56.892 --> 27:58.851
I THINK WE JUST FOUND
OUR GUY'’S HUNTING GROUNDS.

27:58.894 --> 28:00.374
GARCIA: BUT I'’VE GONE
THROUGH ALL THE INSTRUCTORS,

28:00.417 --> 28:02.289
AND NOBODY MATCHES
THE UNSUB'’S PROFILE.

28:02.332 --> 28:05.422
OK, WHAT ABOUT PARENTS
OR FAIRGROUND EMPLOYEES?

28:05.466 --> 28:06.815
NO, NOBODY.
AND THE THING IS,

28:06.859 --> 28:08.295
THAT PLACE IS OPEN
TO THE PUBLIC.

28:08.338 --> 28:09.731
TONS OF PEOPLE GO
IN AND OUT,

28:09.775 --> 28:12.168
IT COULD BE PRACTICALLY
ANYBODY IN TOWN.

28:15.258 --> 28:18.566
WE FOUND THESE
ENCRYPTED EMAILS
IN TIMMY'’S INBOX.

28:18.609 --> 28:20.133
THE DATE OF
THE FIRST ONE

28:20.176 --> 28:22.004
IS THE NIGHT
THE 3 CHILDREN
VANISHED.

28:22.048 --> 28:27.009
